Key Components of Power BI:
1. Power BI Desktop – Used to create reports and dashboards.
2. Power BI Service – Cloud platform for publishing and sharing reports.
3. Power BI Mobile App – View dashboards on smartphones and tablets.
4. Power BI Gateway – Connects on-premises data sources to the cloud.
5. Power BI Report Server – Hosts reports on a company's own servers.

Advantages of Power BI:
1. Easy-to-use drag-and-drop interface.
2. Connects to multiple data sources (Excel, SQL Server, MySQL, Oracle, SharePoint, Azure, Google Analytics, etc.).
3. Interactive and visually appealing dashboards.
4. Real-time data updates.
5. Fast data analysis.
6. AI-powered insights and forecasting.
7. Cloud-based report sharing.
8. Strong security features.
9. Integrates well with Microsoft Office (Excel, Teams, Azure).
10. Cost-effective compared to many other BI tools.

